DiddleBug (2.15)

  * Fixed bug where some sketch data could be lost if alarm sounded
    for the current sketch when DiddleBug is active. (thanks to
    Mike McCollister... again)

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Tue, 22 Feb 2000 06:38:29 -0500

DiddleBug (2.14)

  * Fixed alarm bug where multiple alarms would not display unless
    DiddleBug was the active application.  Thanks to Mattias Lundgren
    for finding the bug.
  * Beta versions of Portugese and Czech translations

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Tue, 22 Feb 2000 05:13:21 -0500

DiddleBug (2.13)

  * Fixed bug where you could not stop the backlinking for plugins if
    Linker is installed.

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Thu, 23 Dec 1999 11:02:22 -0500

DiddleBug (2.12)

  * Added support for Linker.  All records created with IntelliBooger
    plugins now have the option of including a link back to the
    orignal DiddleBug sketch.
  * Beaming!

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Thu, 23 Dec 1999 00:07:01 -0500

DiddleBug (2.11)

  * Fixed bug which caused fatal error if you attempt to transfer
    with no plugins installed.
  * Fixed plugins for Hi-Note to work with new version (2.10) of Hi-Note
  * Added plugins (Event and Float) for Visor enhanced DateBk+.
  * Added plugin for HandBase.

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Mon, 13 Dec 1999 04:38:26 -0500

DiddleBug (2.10)

  * Manual updates by Mari Stoddard
  * Fix cosmetic bug where captured sketch could "leak thru" the controls
    on the bottom of the alarm display (Matt Burleigh)
  * Fixed bug where new changes on an alarm showing current sketch would
    not show in the Alarm Display, and possibly erase the current sketch
    accidentally (Greg Samson and Steve Turczyn)
  * Fixed bug in ImageViewerIII plugin that sometimes caused
    "Index out of range" errors.
  * Fixed display error when alarm is shown while in an application that
    uses greyscale (such as AvantGo).
  * Fix verify confirmation on Delete from alarm screen (John Tsombakos)
  * Added Undo capability to sketches
  * Added plugin for TinyViewer
  * Added plugin for Spec
  * Added plugin for Diddle (Richard Sperko)
  * Added DiddleSnap screen capture hack
  * Japanese translation by KUROSAKA Teruhiko <kuro@a.email.ne.jp>

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Fri, 17 Sep 1999 05:31:45 -0400

DiddleBug (2.9)

  * Fixed a buffer overflow in plugins that I hope will fix some of
    the random problems that have been reported.
  * ImageViewerIII plugin
  * ZipCode Plus plugin (suggested by Victor Hastings)
  * ClipBoard plugin coded by Lonnie Foster
  * Added edit menus to the "Insert Text" dialog (by Lonnie Foster)

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Fri, 27 Aug 1999 05:16:38 -0400

DiddleBug (2.8)

  * Fixed bug where snoozes wouldn't always set. (Bernd Kuemmerlen)

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Fri, 20 Aug 1999 04:57:47 -0400

DiddleBug (2.7)

  * Fixed another cosmetic "sticky-countdown" bug which could occur
    if an alarm sounds while in transfer mode
  * Added a time/date stamp that you can add to the sketch by dragging
    from the alarm bar (Judge Adrian Roden from Down Under)

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Fri, 20 Aug 1999 00:25:10 -0400

DiddleBug (2.6)

  * Re-wrote database code to use compressed records
  * Added an offscreen buffer and dirty flags to speed performance
  * Changed the titlebar buttons and drop-lists to use icons
    (Icons courtesy of Kevin Lo)
  * Confirm screen fill to prevent accidental data loss (Jay Leber)
  * All confirmation screens now have affirmative answer on the left
    (McCollister, Jean, and Schwingeler)
  * Alerts the user when an alarm setting is attempted for earlier than
    the current date/time (Kuai Ser Leng)
  * Hardware button can cycle through sketches (Kevin Lo)
  * Bug where blank sketch is created when deleting from alarm screen and
    diddlebug is not active (Derek Helt and Glenn Garvey)
  * Plugins for Hi-Note (picture and text)
  * Plugin for ToDoPlus (no alarms or sketch data)

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Thu, 19 Aug 1999 06:10:33 -0400

DiddleBug (2.5)

  * Tweaked drawing code to allow taps to make a single dot.
    (Bernd Kuemmerlen)

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Mon,  9 Aug 1999 17:16:08 -0400

DiddleBug (2.4)

  * Smoothing filter didn't (fixed) (McCollister)
  * Sketch marks could be made even on locked sketch (fixed) (Kobi Sapir)
  * Added better looking check mark to flick menu (Frederic Jean)

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Mon,  9 Aug 1999 08:08:52 -0400

DiddleBug (2.3)

  * Fixed bug where datebook-type plugins would add one minute to
    time of the appointment. (E Wong)
  * Fixed bug where DateBook plugin would not set alarm unless you
    enter the DateBook application afterwards
  * Fixed alarm-bar swipe to wait for penUp to initiate action (McCollister)
  * Allow scrolling of the Transfer Pick field with scroll buttons
  * Re-write of pen event handling to make freehand sketching faster
  * Added URL to the no-plugin warning
  * Added ability to mark entries as complete when transferring them
    in the appropriate (ToDo or Floating Event) plugins (Carlos Pereira)
  * New alarm-bar icons for New, Delete, and Clear (thanks to Peder Stray)
  * New alarm-bar icons for lock and toggle (thanks to Horace Ho)
  * New plugin icons for most plugins (thanks to Mark Griswold)
  * New plugin for BrainForest (thanks to Sonny Portacio for the info)
  * New plugins for DateBk3 (events and floating events)
  * New plugin for TealPhone

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Mon,  9 Aug 1999 02:50:43 -0400

DiddleBug (2.2)

  * Fixed yet another "sticky-countdown" bug. (thanks to JM Kline)
  * Added a plugin for Memo Pad.

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Wed,  4 Aug 1999 17:19:29 -0400

DiddleBug (2.1)

  * Enforced lock on alarm time even when "swipe" is applied to the
    alarm bar (McCollister)
  * Fixed bug where alarm bar countdown does not refresh after a
    deletion using the Transfer option (Steve Turczyn)
  * Prevent dismissal of alarm with hardware or silkscreen buttons.
    (Steve Turczyn)
  * Fixed form display bug of alarm box too early (McCollister)
  * Added "left-swipe" on alarm bar to quickly enter Transfer mode.
  * Fixed bug where AlarmTriggered() would not check if window
    was covered before saving screen.  This would cause other
    alarm dialogs to become "pasted" onto the screen in rare instances.
  * Fixed problem when using the character shortcuts with multi-byte
    characters (the pen Medium and Bold settings) (Don Barnett)
  * Re-wrote IntelliBooger to use plugins.
  * Added IB Plugins for ToDo, DateBook, Address, ActionNames, and Supernames.

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Wed,  4 Aug 1999 08:04:12 -0400

DiddleBug (2.0)

  * Changed behavior of locked sketches to allow setting of alarm
    if not already set, while still preventing changing of an already
    set alarm.  (thanks to Alan B. aka "shrink")
  * Added new program icons that accurately represent what a DiddleBug
    looks like. (thanks to Martin Geist for the icons)
  * Changes to screen update code to make DiddleBug less of a battery
    hog. (Peder Stray)
  * Added IntelliBooger(tm) extentions for ToDo and DateBook.  Special
    thanks to Chris Cardone for the idea and consultation on the
    IntelliBooger(tm) concept.  The 2.x series of DiddleBug will
    expand the number and capabilities of the IntelliBooger(tm) extensions.
  * Added shortcut to the "Set Alarm Details" dialog.  Just swipe
    your pen across the alarm bar instead of tapping it.
    (thanks to David Bar-Shain for the idea)
  * Locked reminders will not ask you to confirm twice now when deleted
    (Frederic Jean)

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Wed, 28 Jul 1999 22:02:04 -0400

DiddleBug (1.8)

  * Fixed cosmetic bug where "2weeks" in popup list did not have a space.
  * Removed some gratuitous bolding in the Alarm Set dialog.
    (as suggested by Frederic Jean)
  * Changed behavior of creating a new sketch (hardware button or menu)
    so that no new sketch is created if the current sketch is empty
    and without an alarm. (thanks to Chris Cardone for the suggestion)
  * Locked sketches now warn you if you try to change alarm times
    (as suggested by Frederic Jean)
  * Rewrite of menu shortcut code to support loclization and multi-byte
    fonts.

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Mon, 19 Jul 1999 19:00:05 -0400

DiddleBug (1.7)

  * Fixed hardware button bug that I had accidentally "unfixed" in
    version 1.6.  Thanks to Francisco Sanchez for finding it.
  * Spanish translation by Francisco Sanchez.
  * Allow hardware button to launch other applications
    (as suggested by Damon Meledones)
  * Using Monday as the first day of week is now supported.

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Tue, 13 Jul 1999 05:07:38 -0400

DiddleBug (1.6)

  * Fixed display error on Alarm Form in lower corners (McCollister)
  * Pen style for the Erase mode now toggles independantly of the pens
    for Paint and Smear.  This allows you to easily switch between
    a big eraser and a finer pen. (thanks to Ken PhilPott)
  * The "Big Ok" option in Preferences allows you to dismiss an alarm
    screen popup with a tap anywhere on the screen.
    (thanks to Emory Petrack and Peder Stray for the suggestion)
  * Checks for at least PalmOS version 2.0 and tells the user if using
    an earlier version. (McCollister)
  * Coding changes to support localization
  * Korean (Hangul) localization.  Thanks to Parang <paranbi@email.com>
    for the translation and other work!
  * Fixed bug where unlocking a sketch would not always remove the
    key icon immediately (when no alarm was set)

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Mon,  5 Jul 1999 20:15:02 -0400

DiddleBug (1.5)

  * Fixed bug where alarm would not sound under the following
    circumstances: (Thanks to E Wong for finding the bug)
    (1) Palm is powered off while DiddleBug is active
    (2) Palm is powered on again using a hardware button immediately
        after the alarm was scheduled to sound but before the 1-minute
        resolution of the Alarm interrupt in sleep mode caught it.
  * Fixed bug that could cause Fatal Exceptions when toggling the
    titlebar quickly. (E Wong)
  * Added "Bold" entry to the Pen list for a 3x3 pen.
    (Thanks to Bruce Cameron for the suggestion)
  * Added ability to lock sketches
  * Added snoozing to the alarm display
  * Added optional drop-down lists for selections from titlebar buttons

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Mon, 28 Jun 1999 08:58:57 -0400

DiddleBug (1.4)

  * Time and Date formats now used from global Palm preferences
  * Current time shown in titlebar of main form
    (as suggested by Bruce Cameron)
  * Add "Custom..." to countdown popup list to allow setting of odd
    countdown times like 13:23 (suggested by Peder Stray)
  * Added "BiWeekly" to the list of repeat modes

-- Mitch Blevins <mblevin@debian.org>        Wed, 23 Jun 1999 19:02:03 -0400

DiddleBug (1.3)

  * Alarm would not sound when set as Absolute and remains on the
    current screen until the alarm time (Thanks to Shel Weisel)

